### [Psalms Chapter 139](../../../bib/kjv/psa139.htm#001.md)

[Psalms](../../../bib/kjv/psa001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">psa 139:0</span></span>

Overview

[Psa 139:1](../../../bib/kjv/psa139.htm#001.md), David praises God for his
all-seeing providence; [Psa 139:17](../../../bib/kjv/psa139.htm#017.md),
and for his infinite mercies; [Psa
139:19](../../../bib/kjv/psa139.htm#019.md), He defies the wicked; [Psa
139:23](../../../bib/kjv/psa139.htm#023.md), He prays for sincerity.

This Psalm is supposed to have been composed by David when made king of
Israel; though some think it was written by him when accused of
traitorous designs against Saul. It is a most sublime ode on the wisdom,
knowledge, presence, and justice of God. the sentiments are grand, the
style highly elevated, and the images various, beautiful, and
impressive.

