<span class="margnote"><span id="an_009">psa 139:9</span></span>

If I take: Light has been proved, by many experiments, to travel at the
astonishing rate of 194,188 miles in one second of time; and comes from
the sun to the earth, a distance of 95,513,794 miles in 8 minutes and
nearly 12 seconds! But, could I even fly upon the wings or rays of the
morning light, which diffuses itself with such velocity over the globe
from east to west, instead of being beyond Thy reach, or by this sudden
transition be able to escape Thy notice, Thy arm could still at pleasure
prevent or arrest my progress, and I should still be encircled with the
immensity of Thy essence. The sentiment in this noble passage is
remarkably striking and the description truly sublime.

